@node Configuration keys table
@section Configuration keys table

Every key recognized in @file{src/main/backend/application.ini}.

@subsection Required

@multitable @columnfractions .30 .70
@headitem Key @tab Purpose
@item @code{DatabaseHost} @tab Postgres host.
@item @code{DatabasePort} @tab Postgres port.
@item @code{DatabaseName} @tab Database name (typically @code{ownsona}).
@item @code{DatabaseUser} @tab Application role.
@item @code{DatabasePassword} @tab Password for the application role.
@item @code{OWNSONA_API_TOKEN} @tab Bearer token MCP clients must present.
@item @code{EMBEDDING_API_KEY} @tab API key for the embeddings endpoint.
@item @code{EMBEDDING_ENDPOINT} @tab Full URL of the @code{/embeddings} endpoint.
@item @code{EMBEDDING_MODEL} @tab Embedding model identifier.
@item @code{EMBEDDING_DIMENSIONS} @tab Vector length. Must match @code{vector(N)} column.
@end multitable

@subsection Optional with defaults

@multitable @columnfractions .30 .15 .55
@headitem Key @tab Default @tab Purpose
@item @code{DatabaseType} @tab @code{PostgreSQL} @tab Kiss DB driver type (only PostgreSQL supported).
@item @code{DatabaseConnectionParameters} @tab (none) @tab Appended to JDBC URL.
@item @code{OWNSONA_USER_ID} @tab @code{default} @tab User-id stamped on every memory.
@item @code{EMBEDDING_PROVIDER} @tab @code{openai} @tab Provider name recorded per row.
@item @code{DEFAULT_RECALL_LIMIT} @tab @code{8} @tab Default @code{limit} for @code{recall}.
@item @code{MAX_RECALL_LIMIT} @tab @code{50} @tab Hard cap on @code{limit}.
@item @code{MAX_TEXT_CHARS} @tab @code{16000} @tab Hard cap on memory text length.
@item @code{MAX_BATCH_SIZE} @tab @code{200} @tab Max items per @code{remember_batch}.
@item @code{REEMBED_ON_STARTUP} @tab @code{false} @tab Triggers the re-embed walker. Auto-flipped after success.
@item @code{MaxWorkerThreads} @tab @code{30} @tab Kiss tunable: concurrent request cap.
@item @code{UserInactiveSeconds} @tab @code{900} @tab Kiss tunable: session inactivity timeout.
@end multitable

@subsection Connection pool tunables (Kiss-provided)

Rarely changed.  Defaults come from c3p0; override when your workload
calls for it.

@multitable @columnfractions .40 .60
@headitem Key @tab Purpose
@item @code{DatabaseMinPoolSize} @tab Minimum connections kept hot.
@item @code{DatabaseInitialPoolSize} @tab Pool size at startup.
@item @code{DatabaseMaxPoolSize} @tab Hard cap on pool size.
@item @code{DatabaseAcquireIncrement} @tab Connections added per growth step.
@item @code{DatabaseCheckoutTimeout} @tab Millis to wait before timing out.
@item @code{DatabaseMaxStatements} @tab Prepared-statement cache size.
@item @code{DatabaseIdleTestPeriod} @tab Seconds between idle-connection tests.
@item @code{DatabaseMaxIdleTime} @tab Seconds before removing idle connections.
@end multitable

