@node Environment variables
@section Environment variables

Most settings live in @file{application.ini} or the CLI's
@file{config.ini}, but a few work via environment:

@multitable @columnfractions .35 .65
@headitem Variable @tab Purpose
@item @code{OWNSONA_TEST_DATABASE_URL} @tab JDBC URL for a separate test database.  Gates the integration tests in @code{sql/run_tests.sh}; absent = skip.
@item @code{OWNSONA_API_TOKEN} @tab Used by @file{sql/smoke_test.sh} when invoked from the shell.
@item @code{OWNSONA_SERVER} @tab CLI override for @code{server_url}.
@item @code{OWNSONA_TOKEN} @tab CLI override for @code{token}.
@item @code{OWNSONA_CONFIG} @tab CLI override for the config-file path.
@item @code{OWNSONA_LLM_API_KEY} @tab CLI: API key for the @code{teach} LLM.
@item @code{OWNSONA_LLM_MODEL} @tab CLI: model name for the @code{teach} LLM.
@item @code{OWNSONA_LLM_BASE_URL} @tab CLI: base URL for the @code{teach} chat-completion endpoint.
@item @code{OWNSONA_SUBJECT} @tab CLI: how @code{teach} should refer to you in extracted facts.
@end multitable

@node Kiss framework references
@section Kiss framework references
@cindex Kiss
@cindex Kiss framework

OwnSona is built on the
@uref{https://kissweb.org, Kiss web development framework}, an
open-source Java full-stack framework.  Kiss provides:

@itemize @bullet
@item The @code{MainServlet} container glue that loads
@file{application.ini}, sets up the C3P0 connection pool, and exposes
the @code{Connection}/@code{Record} database API used throughout
OwnSona.
@item The @code{MCPServerBase} class @code{MCPServer.java} extends ---
parses JSON-RPC envelopes, dispatches to tool handlers, formats tool
results.
@item The custom @code{bld} build script (no Maven, no Gradle).
@item The @code{org.kissweb.json} classes used for all server-side
JSON manipulation.
@item The @code{IniFile} class @code{ApplicationIniWriter} works
alongside.
@end itemize

Where to read more:

@multitable @columnfractions .35 .65
@headitem Resource @tab URL
@item Kiss home page         @tab @uref{https://kissweb.org}
@item Kiss source            @tab @uref{https://github.com/blakemcbride/Kiss}
@item Kiss user manual       @tab @uref{https://kissweb.org/manual.html}
@item Frontend JSDoc         @tab @uref{https://kissweb.org/jsdoc/}
@item Backend JavaDoc        @tab generated locally with @code{./bld javadoc} into @file{work/javadoc/}
@end multitable

OwnSona's relationship to Kiss: OwnSona is a Kiss @emph{application}.
The Kiss source ships inside the OwnSona repo at
@file{src/main/core/} and is the part of the codebase OwnSona @b{must
not modify} (rebuilding from the upstream Kiss release is the way to
update Kiss itself).  OwnSona's own code lives in
@file{src/main/precompiled/} and @file{src/main/backend/}.

When in doubt about where a feature lives --- the database pool, the
INI loader, the servlet base class --- start by asking whether it's a
Kiss feature.  Most ``how does the framework do X'' answers are in
Kiss's manual, not in this one.
